{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"865e680f-950c-4e4a-bcac-ea160770ab52","content":"Use `dotnet test --hotreload` — it's built into the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner your project already uses (configured in `global.json`). It watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically.\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis will keep running, and every time you save a file it re-runs the affected tests.\n\n**About the failing test:** `RemoveStock` never throws — it just subtracts without checking. You'll need to add a guard, e.g.:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply that fix so you can see it pass with hot reload?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"46a5ce27-93cc-4ecf-8618-dc6146b0f056","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for their test project. With .NET and MSTest using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (as configured in global.json), they can use `dotnet test --hotreload` or `dotnet watch test` to get hot reload.\n\nActually, let me think about this. With .NET 10 and Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the recommended approach is `dotnet test --hotreload` which re-runs tests automatically when files change. Alternatively, `dotnet watch test` works too.\n\nLet me provide the guidance on how to set up hot reload and also note the bug in their code (RemoveStock doesn't throw when quantity exceeds available).","outputTokens":374,"requestId":"A80D:2843AB:65ADC95:6E24A1B:6A034B81"},"id":"04e6ada4-ec74-452f-9825-3315545d0132","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:47:24.724Z","parentId":"663a36d4-febf-45e9-8c99-2490ca7b11a8"}
